She heard you and
wanted to know.

505
00:23:30,310 --> 00:23:31,618
Well heavens!

506
00:23:31,645 --> 00:23:34,396
Charlie Cline!

507
00:23:34,556 --> 00:23:35,730
I can't believe I'm
squeezin on ya!

508
00:23:35,890 --> 00:23:37,048
It's actually Dick.

509
00:23:37,109 --> 00:23:37,807
You need something, buddy?

510
00:23:37,901 --> 00:23:38,975
Baby come here.

511
00:23:39,069 --> 00:23:40,460
This... This is
Patsy Cline's husband.

512
00:23:40,487 --> 00:23:41,385
Charlie Dick.

513
00:23:41,446 --> 00:23:43,905
Mooney Lynn.

514
00:23:44,065 --> 00:23:45,799
Patsy heard you on the Jamboree
and was hoping you'd come by

515
00:23:45,826 --> 00:23:47,133
and visit her tomorrow?

516
00:23:47,160 --> 00:23:49,244
What?

517
00:23:49,404 --> 00:23:50,637
Hey well she'll be there.

518
00:23:50,664 --> 00:23:52,822
Mh-hmm.

519
00:23:52,916 --> 00:23:56,159
[NURSE] You going to
behave today?"

520
00:23:56,253 --> 00:23:58,586
Come on in.

521
00:23:58,747 --> 00:23:59,996
You got a vistor.

522
00:24:00,090 --> 00:24:03,333
Oh hey...
you must be Loretta.

523
00:24:03,427 --> 00:24:04,834
Well come on now.

524
00:24:04,928 --> 00:24:06,152
How we gonna visit if you
standing in the hall?

525
00:24:06,179 --> 00:24:08,321
Oh. [LAUGHS]

526
00:24:08,348 --> 00:24:09,989
Go ahead and shut the
door if you don't mind.

527
00:24:10,017 --> 00:24:12,675
Those for me?

528
00:24:12,769 --> 00:24:14,752
Um.

529
00:24:14,813 --> 00:24:17,439
Oh.

530
00:24:17,599 --> 00:24:21,684
I don't even like roses.

531
00:24:21,778 --> 00:24:22,777
Toss those.

532
00:24:22,937 --> 00:24:24,279
Put 'em in the
sink or something.

533
00:24:24,439 --> 00:24:26,990
Yours will look real
pretty in that vase.

534
00:24:32,205 --> 00:24:34,180
Miss Cline, I hope you're
not angry with me.

535
00:24:34,207 --> 00:24:37,350
Angry? Why? And call me Patsy.

536
00:24:37,377 --> 00:24:40,370
I wou... for singing your song.

537
00:24:40,464 --> 00:24:41,354
Not at all.

538
00:24:41,381 --> 00:24:42,856
I... I thought it was real sweet.

539
00:24:42,883 --> 00:24:45,358
I wanted to thank you for it.

540
00:24:45,385 --> 00:24:47,785
Doo told me I was being crazy.

541
00:24:47,846 --> 00:24:50,713
You think I invited you here
to yell at you or something?

542
00:24:50,807 --> 00:24:51,973
Well I don't know.

543
00:24:52,133 --> 00:24:53,791
I don't always think
before I do things.

544
00:24:53,852 --> 00:24:56,144
Doo says causes all
sorts of problems.

545
00:24:56,304 --> 00:25:00,982
Well now I gotta
know who Doo is.

546
00:25:01,142 --> 00:25:04,652
Oh, Doo's my husband.

547
00:25:04,813 --> 00:25:07,714
Well, uh... Mooney most people
call him on account of he used

548
00:25:07,741 --> 00:25:09,473
to deliver moonshine back where
he is from in Butcher Holler.

549
00:25:09,534 --> 00:25:11,401
But before that his daddy
called him Doolittle.

550
00:25:11,495 --> 00:25:12,827
I think because he is
such a little thing.

551
00:25:12,987 --> 00:25:15,479
Sure did grow though.

552
00:25:15,540 --> 00:25:17,481
Still, I just call him Doo.

553
00:25:17,542 --> 00:25:20,727
Well you sure got
folks talking, sugar.

554
00:25:20,754 --> 00:25:22,153
Now your with the
Wilburns I hear.

555
00:25:22,214 --> 00:25:23,246
Uh... well sorta.

556
00:25:23,340 --> 00:25:24,747
Doyle's been
working with me on

557
00:25:24,841 --> 00:25:27,066
songwriting but... but I'm only
here 'cause of Doo.

558
00:25:27,094 --> 00:25:28,343
How you figure?

559
00:25:28,503 --> 00:25:29,511
Well he's the one that
wanted me to sing.

560
00:25:29,671 --> 00:25:32,071
You don't wanna sing?

561
00:25:32,099 --> 00:25:32,847
No, I like it.

562
00:25:33,007 --> 00:25:34,590
Just it don't make no sense

563
00:25:34,684 --> 00:25:36,576
anybody pay to see me is all.

564
00:25:36,603 --> 00:25:39,354
Ain't nothing special.

565
00:25:39,514 --> 00:25:41,080
So you just do whatever
Doo tells you?

566
00:25:41,108 --> 00:25:47,420
You ain't got no drive
of your own?

567
00:25:47,447 --> 00:25:49,756
I was real young when we met.

568
00:25:49,783 --> 00:25:52,349
And he'd already served in the
army and traveled around,

569
00:25:52,411 --> 00:25:54,035
lived a lot of life.

570
00:25:54,195 --> 00:25:57,205
I was just, Loretta.

571
00:25:57,365 --> 00:25:59,541
Felt real special he
even noticed me.

572
00:25:59,701 --> 00:26:00,375
How old were you?

573
00:26:00,535 --> 00:26:02,118
Fourteen.

574
00:26:02,212 --> 00:26:03,286
Well I don't mean to sound
like I got regrets.

575
00:26:03,380 --> 00:26:05,271
I... I love him.

576
00:26:05,298 --> 00:26:07,531
He works hard.

577
00:26:07,592 --> 00:26:09,108
Takes good care of us.

578
00:26:09,136 --> 00:26:14,464
It's just, well it ain't easy,
disagreeing with him.

579
00:26:14,558 --> 00:26:16,950
Shit sugar, disagreein'
ain't ever easy.

580
00:26:16,977 --> 00:26:20,954
Doesn't mean it ain't necessary.

581
00:26:20,981 --> 00:26:22,397
Hey let's say Doo
never happened.

582
00:26:22,557 --> 00:26:24,232
What do you want?

583
00:26:24,392 --> 00:26:26,142
I don't know I guess,

584
00:26:26,236 --> 00:26:29,904
I only ever thought about
wanting to be a mama.

585
00:26:30,064 --> 00:26:31,388
Want my family to
be taken care of.

586
00:26:31,450 --> 00:26:33,724
And I want everyone to know
how much I love 'em.

587
00:26:33,785 --> 00:26:36,652
Alright well lets think
about this a little more.

588
00:26:36,746 --> 00:26:39,489
Let's say all thats guaranteed.

589
00:26:39,583 --> 00:26:41,565
You ain't got to worry
about nothing no more.

590
00:26:41,626 --> 00:26:43,476
What do <i>you</i> want?

591
00:26:43,503 --> 00:26:48,089
I guess I want the same
thing for the world.

592
00:26:48,249 --> 00:26:53,410
There's so much
heartache out there.

593
00:26:53,472 --> 00:26:54,262
I start to think about it,

594
00:26:54,422 --> 00:26:56,489
I just want to die.

595
00:26:56,516 --> 00:26:58,749
I guess I just want everyone
to know their loved.

596
00:26:58,810 --> 00:27:00,935
Someone cares about them.

597
00:27:01,095 --> 00:27:03,754
I just don't want no one feeling
alone when they go to sleep at

598
00:27:03,815 --> 00:27:05,940
night even if they are.

599
00:27:06,100 --> 00:27:11,095
Sounds like you was always
gonna be a singer.

600
00:27:11,156 --> 00:27:13,114
The Wilburns offered me a
management contract.

601
00:27:13,274 --> 00:27:14,449
Well hey that's great!

602
00:27:14,609 --> 00:27:16,692
Well it could be.

603
00:27:16,786 --> 00:27:18,344
Well listen if you're
worried about the fact

604
00:27:18,371 --> 00:27:20,847
that they're musicians too,
sure, there's plenty of stone

605
00:27:20,874 --> 00:27:22,849
cold dumdums in this business.

606
00:27:22,876 --> 00:27:26,628
But I tell you my Randy's a
picker and hiring him is the

607
00:27:26,788 --> 00:27:28,946
best business decision
I ever made.

608
00:27:29,007 --> 00:27:31,115
[CHURCH BELLS TOLL]

609
00:27:31,176 --> 00:27:33,192
Oh lord, it's late.

610
00:27:33,220 --> 00:27:34,694
You alright, little gal?

611
00:27:34,721 --> 00:27:37,363
Sure, just, Doo's gonna be
looking for his supper.

612
00:27:37,390 --> 00:27:41,309
Well alright now, give the
Cline a shove inside.

613
00:27:41,469 --> 00:27:42,310
Alright, ready?

614
00:27:42,470 --> 00:27:43,311
MmmHmm

615
00:27:43,471 --> 00:27:44,704
Alright here we go.

616
00:27:44,731 --> 00:27:47,774
Oh, hey now.

617
00:27:48,693 --> 00:27:51,060
What are you looking for?

618
00:27:51,154 --> 00:27:53,947
Dinner, damnit!

619
00:27:57,485 --> 00:27:59,160
You been at the hospital
this whole time?

620
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:01,721
Patsy's real sweet.

621
00:28:01,748 --> 00:28:06,242
Thank I finally got
a friend here.

622
00:28:06,336 --> 00:28:08,744
Did Charlie give
you a ride home?

623
00:28:08,838 --> 00:28:11,655
She gave me money for a taxi.

624
00:28:11,716 --> 00:28:12,507
I don't like that.

625
00:28:12,667 --> 00:28:13,991
You taking a taxi by yourself.

626
00:28:14,052 --> 00:28:15,401
Well it seems like there's
a lot you don't like.

627
00:28:15,428 --> 00:28:16,419
Oh yeah?

628
00:28:16,513 --> 00:28:18,680
You looked at
that contract yet?

629
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:20,089
From the Wilburns?

630
00:28:20,183 --> 00:28:22,241
Sure.

631
00:28:22,269 --> 00:28:24,577
Well? I wanna sign it.

632
00:28:24,604 --> 00:28:25,595
Not yet.

633
00:28:25,689 --> 00:28:27,021
Why?

634
00:28:27,181 --> 00:28:30,858
Loretta, you got a
fifth grade education,

635
00:28:31,019 --> 00:28:35,113
what the hell you know
about contracts?

636
00:28:42,289 --> 00:28:43,946
I'm frying liver tonight.

637
00:28:44,040 --> 00:28:45,856
Won't take long.

638
00:28:45,917 --> 00:28:47,875
See that it don't.

639
00:28:48,036 --> 00:28:50,503
[SIGHS]

640
00:28:51,756 --> 00:28:54,757
[MUSIC CUE]

641
00:29:37,177 --> 00:29:38,985
Looks real fair to me.

642
00:29:39,012 --> 00:29:40,987
I'd ask 'em to make it two
years, instead of three.

643
00:29:41,014 --> 00:29:43,080
But if I was you
I would sign it.

644
00:29:43,141 --> 00:29:44,490
Can I tell Doo that?

645
00:29:44,517 --> 00:29:45,933
Well honey he's your husband.

646
00:29:46,094 --> 00:29:47,084
You can tell him
whatever you want.

647
00:29:47,145 --> 00:29:48,585
[DOOR OPENS]

648
00:29:48,647 --> 00:29:50,254
Afternoon Miss Patsy.

649
00:29:50,315 --> 00:29:51,588
Hey there Gertie,
you met Loretta?

650
00:29:51,650 --> 00:29:53,590
I have.

651
00:29:53,652 --> 00:29:55,351
I heard you on the Opry last
week, you were great!

652
00:29:55,445 --> 00:29:56,927
Well thank you.

653
00:29:56,988 --> 00:29:58,446
Now what form of torture you
bringing me today, girl?

654
00:29:58,606 --> 00:30:01,616
Ohh Miss Pasty.

655
00:30:01,776 --> 00:30:04,193
You make sure she eats
this, Miss Loretta.

656
00:30:04,287 --> 00:30:05,695
I promise.

657
00:30:05,789 --> 00:30:06,954
I'm going to grab you
some ice water.

658
00:30:07,115 --> 00:30:08,956
MmmHmm

659
00:30:09,117 --> 00:30:11,184
Dump that in the commode.

660
00:30:11,211 --> 00:30:12,126
Patsy, that's good food!

661
00:30:12,286 --> 00:30:14,020
Then you eat it.

662
00:30:14,047 --> 00:30:15,538
Charlie was supposed to smuggle
me a cheeseburger but

663
00:30:15,632 --> 00:30:16,706
Julie got sick.

664
00:30:16,800 --> 00:30:18,691
Now come on, grab my wheelchair.

665
00:30:18,718 --> 00:30:19,616
You...

666
00:30:19,678 --> 00:30:21,469
[SIGHS]

667
00:30:22,639 --> 00:30:24,030
Well, I ain't got a car
and you can't drive

668
00:30:24,057 --> 00:30:24,972
so what are we doing?

669
00:30:25,133 --> 00:30:27,049
Rotiers is down
the street relax.

670
00:30:27,143 --> 00:30:28,309
Miss Patsy, you sure
wolfed that food fast.

671
00:30:28,469 --> 00:30:29,885
Oh I couldn't help myself.

672
00:30:29,979 --> 00:30:32,371
Courtyard's only open
another twenty minutes.

673
00:30:32,399 --> 00:30:34,540
See you soon.

674
00:30:34,976 --> 00:30:36,392
Lord have mercy this is good.

675
00:30:36,486 --> 00:30:38,711
See it's going to be
downhill the whole way back.

676
00:30:38,738 --> 00:30:41,380
How long you been with Charlie?

677
00:30:41,408 --> 00:30:43,140
Well that depends on when
you start countin'.

678
00:30:43,201 --> 00:30:45,476
Been married a little
over two years.

679
00:30:45,537 --> 00:30:47,311
Of course I had to
divorce Gerald first.

680
00:30:47,372 --> 00:30:48,663
And your babies?

681
00:30:48,823 --> 00:30:50,556
Charlie's.
Gerald didn't want any.

682
00:30:50,583 --> 00:30:52,558
Didn't want me singing neither.

683
00:30:52,585 --> 00:30:54,060
That don't make no sense.

684
00:30:54,087 --> 00:30:57,246
No, it did not.

685
00:30:57,340 --> 00:30:59,323
Hey, how'd you even
start singing anyway?

686
00:30:59,384 --> 00:31:02,068
Singing long before Gerald.

687
00:31:02,095 --> 00:31:03,511
Fourteen I started.

688
00:31:03,671 --> 00:31:04,904
Your mama and daddy
singers or something?

689
00:31:04,931 --> 00:31:06,681
My daddy had a real fine voice.

690
00:31:06,841 --> 00:31:08,908
Still does for all I know.

691
00:31:08,935 --> 00:31:11,001
Didn't do it
professional though.

692
00:31:11,062 --> 00:31:14,247
I guess I got him to thank
for the reason I started.

693
00:31:14,274 --> 00:31:15,748
Him running off.

694
00:31:15,775 --> 00:31:17,600
Had to help mama pay
the bills some kinda way.

695
00:31:17,694 --> 00:31:18,100
Here you go.

696
00:31:18,194 --> 00:31:18,860
Thank you.

697
00:31:19,020 --> 00:31:20,194
Welcome.

698
00:31:20,354 --> 00:31:21,771
Hey.

699
00:31:21,865 --> 00:31:26,016
I went straight from daddy's
house right to Doo's.

700
00:31:26,077 --> 00:31:27,851
I don't know what I would have
done without him there to talk

701
00:31:27,912 --> 00:31:29,203
to people for me.

702
00:31:29,363 --> 00:31:31,097
I never had any
problems talking.

703
00:31:31,124 --> 00:31:34,600
Course everybody around town
figured was handing out hum jobs

704
00:31:34,627 --> 00:31:36,527
like business cards.

705
00:31:36,588 --> 00:31:38,045
Hum jobs?

706
00:31:38,206 --> 00:31:41,290
Yeah it's when you
use your mouth.

707
00:31:41,384 --> 00:31:46,279
Down there.

708
00:31:46,306 --> 00:31:47,388
There's a name for that?

709
00:31:47,548 --> 00:31:49,540
Of course. They've
got a lot of 'em.

710
00:31:49,601 --> 00:31:52,560
Lets see there's
header, tongue party,

711
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:56,046
french tricks, lip service.

712
00:31:56,107 --> 00:32:03,462
Pricknic, lunch box,
gum job, goop gobbler.

713
00:32:03,490 --> 00:32:04,721
You... you're making these up.

714
00:32:04,783 --> 00:32:07,224
Gobbledegoop, kowtow cow.

715
00:32:07,285 --> 00:32:08,301
Woo!

716
00:32:08,328 --> 00:32:09,560
Thanks Miss Pasty.

717
00:32:09,621 --> 00:32:12,805
Knob bobbin'. Ham sandwich.
Man eatin'.

718
00:32:12,832 --> 00:32:14,290
Patsy!
[LAUGHING]

719
00:32:16,085 --> 00:32:17,919
Hello.

720
00:32:18,079 --> 00:32:19,145
Hello.

721
00:32:19,172 --> 00:32:23,499
803 Maple Street please.

722
00:32:23,593 --> 00:32:26,410
Uh, wait can we make a
different stop first?

723
00:32:26,471 --> 00:32:31,006
Alright. Wash up,
babies, food's here!

724
00:32:32,093 --> 00:32:33,768
I called Patsy's room and
Charlie said you left hours ago!

725
00:32:33,928 --> 00:32:35,511
These kids are near starvin!

726
00:32:35,605 --> 00:32:37,087
Well you're gonna have
to learn to throw

727
00:32:37,148 --> 00:32:38,331
something together if I'm
gonna be out on the road.

728
00:32:38,358 --> 00:32:41,016
Where the hell you been?

729
00:32:41,110 --> 00:32:42,276
I stopped by the Wilburns
on the way home.

730
00:32:42,436 --> 00:32:44,094
To drop off the contract.

731
00:32:44,155 --> 00:32:47,006
You did what?

732
00:32:47,033 --> 00:32:48,174
Their mama's real sweet.

733
00:32:48,201 --> 00:32:49,283
She put plates together.

734
00:32:49,443 --> 00:32:50,509
Pork chops.
They're a little cold, but...

735
00:32:50,537 --> 00:32:52,203
What do you...
[PASTY] Doo!

736
00:32:57,544 --> 00:32:59,201
We talked about this.

737
00:32:59,295 --> 00:33:00,795
I gave it to Patsy to look at.

738
00:33:00,955 --> 00:33:02,779
She said she thought
it was real fair.

739
00:33:02,841 --> 00:33:04,690
What good goddamned thing
does Patsy have to do

740
00:33:04,717 --> 00:33:06,116
with any of this?

741
00:33:06,177 --> 00:33:07,784
You said it'd be a good
idea to get an opinion

742
00:33:07,846 --> 00:33:08,694
from a professional.

743
00:33:08,721 --> 00:33:09,862
She's a professional.

744
00:33:09,889 --> 00:33:10,713
No I didn't say nothin'
to anything...

745
00:33:10,807 --> 00:33:11,530
- Yes you did.
- No I did not!

746
00:33:11,558 --> 00:33:12,531
Sure you did!

747
00:33:12,559 --> 00:33:14,367
Yes last night right before bed.

748
00:33:14,394 --> 00:33:17,144
Don't you remember?

749
00:33:23,361 --> 00:33:25,378
I ain't never lied
to Doo before.

750
00:33:25,405 --> 00:33:26,303
Never.

751
00:33:26,364 --> 00:33:27,488
There. Hold still.

752
00:33:27,648 --> 00:33:32,309
Am I going to hell?

753
00:33:32,370 --> 00:33:33,903
For lyin' to your husband?

754
00:33:33,997 --> 00:33:36,706
Every last girl I know
will see you there.

755
00:33:37,250 --> 00:33:38,332
He's so mad.

756
00:33:38,492 --> 00:33:39,500
He was supposed to
drive me to this gig

757
00:33:39,660 --> 00:33:40,668
I got in Knoxville
tomorrow night and

758
00:33:40,828 --> 00:33:43,729
he flat told me to
take the bus alone.

759
00:33:43,756 --> 00:33:45,080
Want one of the
Wilburns take you?

760
00:33:45,174 --> 00:33:47,341
No they're already
on the road.

761
00:33:47,501 --> 00:33:49,919
I ain't never taken a bus alone.

762
00:33:50,013 --> 00:33:53,556
I ain't ever even
played a show alone.

763
00:33:55,268 --> 00:33:58,835
That don't even look like
I'm wearing make-up at all.

764
00:33:58,897 --> 00:34:00,596
Now listen I ain't
gonna make a habit out

765
